    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-13T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-13T13:00:00-05:00" n="381"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d381">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Stam, John C./8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-13T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 13, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>384. Nanking’s 84, December 13, 7 p.m.,<note n="80" xml:id="d381fn80">Not
                        printed.</note> reporting that the bodies of Mr. and Mrs. Stam have been
                    found but that the baby has not been found.</p>
                <pb facs="0570" n="480" xml:id="pg_480"/>
                <p>Department assumes that Legation will make immediate representations to the
                    Chinese Government expressing this Government’s deep concern, and requesting
                    that prompt and vigorous steps be taken to effect the rescue of the child, if
                    alive, and to apprehend and punish the culprits in accordance with law.</p>
                <p>Report by telegraph.</p>
                <p>Department has informed Stam’s father of Nanking’s telegram.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
